@Eric 
I really wanted it to be DEFER, not DETER, because of Gilbert and Sullivan’s Lord High Executioner. 

I also really wanted “dark side of the moon” to be BARE. I get why it’s MARE, but I find mine funnier.

@JenB 

I thought you were saying that you flew through the puzzle.  

Definitely not my experience!!

@Mike 
I love your rye sense of humor.


The emus appreciate it also.

@Al  in Pittsburgh 
Because there is a good chance that there may be someone out there who wasn’t watching televised political debates in 1968, I thought I would provide a link which provides a bit of background about your comment. I certainly am not endorsing either of these two characters nor the publication involved, but I thought this article presented some of the issues going on at that time.

